1
00:00:41,741 --> 00:00:44,608
Mr. Campbell. Mr. Campbell.

2
00:00:46,446 --> 00:00:48,209
I got your hot cocoa.

3
00:00:52,285 --> 00:00:53,411
Wonderful.

4
00:00:53,520 --> 00:00:57,183
I just got back from lunch,
and Mr. Pryce wants to see you.

5
00:00:58,958 --> 00:01:01,426
- It's instant.
- It's from the diner.

6
00:01:01,795 --> 00:01:02,989
I don't know how you can tell.

7
00:01:03,096 --> 00:01:06,361
You can tell because
they use water instead of milk.

8
00:01:07,700 --> 00:01:10,498
It's warmer outside. It's ridiculous.

9
00:01:11,604 --> 00:01:14,767
The building will take care of it.
They always do.

10
00:01:16,076 --> 00:01:19,944
Sorry about that.
This really is hitting the spot.

11
00:01:27,554 --> 00:01:28,748
Come in.

12
00:01:32,459 --> 00:01:33,824
Have a seat.

13
00:01:37,831 --> 00:01:41,062
I believe I have
what is rather disappointing news.

14
00:01:41,835 --> 00:01:43,735
It's been decided that Mr. Cosgrove

15
00:01:43,837 --> 00:01:47,398
will be made senior vice president
in charge of account services,

16
00:01:47,507 --> 00:01:50,567
and you will be made
head of account management.

17
00:01:52,812 --> 00:01:53,801
Really?

18
00:01:53,913 --> 00:01:56,711
This is not to ignore
that you've distinguished yourself

19
00:01:56,816 --> 00:01:59,580
and been of great service to the company.

20
00:01:59,719 --> 00:02:02,984
What is it based on?
Our billings are neck and neck.

21
00:02:04,090 --> 00:02:08,891
In fact, I think I've done a lot with
what I was given in this arbitrary scheme.

22
00:02:09,462 --> 00:02:11,191
It's become apparent

23
00:02:12,098 --> 00:02:16,660
that you are excellent at making the clients
feel their needs are being met,

24
00:02:17,170 --> 00:02:20,003
but Mr. Cosgrove has the rare gift
of making them feel

25
00:02:20,106 --> 00:02:22,267
as if they haven't any needs.

26
00:02:24,544 --> 00:02:26,876
- I see.
- I improved your title.

27
00:02:28,414 --> 00:02:32,145
And you tell your clients
there'll be no need to be deprecating.

28
00:02:32,252 --> 00:02:36,018
- Bert and Roger know about this?
- This is under my authority.

29
00:02:36,756 --> 00:02:40,419
And I have to commend you
on taking it as well as you have.

30
00:02:48,635 --> 00:02:51,661
- I hope this was a difficult decision.
- It was.

31
00:03:05,852 --> 00:03:07,285
There you go.

32
00:03:19,666 --> 00:03:22,362
- Where are you going?
- I don't feel well.

33
00:03:24,404 --> 00:03:26,235
Why did you pick that place?

34
00:03:26,339 --> 00:03:29,638
I don't know why a lunch counter
is any better than eating at your desk.

35
00:03:29,742 --> 00:03:31,642
Well, you could've joined me for a drink.

36
00:03:31,744 --> 00:03:34,770
I can drink at my desk if I want to,
and I'm not out $1.25.

37
00:03:34,881 --> 00:03:38,544
I'm sorry I'm not as stimulating
a lunch companion as Doug.

38
00:03:39,118 --> 00:03:43,521
- It's Duck, and I work most lunches.
- Well, I don't like his aftershave.

39
00:03:43,957 --> 00:03:47,017
I can smell it on you, and I can smell it
in the bathroom in the morning.

40
00:03:47,126 --> 00:03:48,957
What's wrong with him?

41
00:03:49,095 --> 00:03:53,031
Nothing. I don't even know
why I'm weighing in on men right now.

42
00:03:53,166 --> 00:03:55,999
I think it's good
that you're being picky, finally.

43
00:03:56,135 --> 00:03:58,467
Well, there's nothing around
but married ones.

44
00:03:58,571 --> 00:04:01,369
I mean, we can't all
throw caution to the wind.

45
00:04:01,474 --> 00:04:03,339
But Duck's not married.

46
00:04:04,344 --> 00:04:06,335
Then why are you with him?

47
00:04:11,217 --> 00:04:14,448
- Well, this is me. You working late tonight?
- I don't know yet.

48
00:04:14,554 --> 00:04:16,044
- Okay.
- Bye.

49
00:04:19,559 --> 00:04:23,325
Wow. Van Cleef.
How very Jane Siegel-Sterling.

50
00:04:24,831 --> 00:04:28,096
- They're blue and they're new.
- She's trying.

51
00:04:28,901 --> 00:04:30,869
You always take her side.

52
00:04:32,639 --> 00:04:33,867
I do not.

53
00:04:35,341 --> 00:04:37,605
She started giving me advice.

54
00:04:38,478 --> 00:04:41,811
"Don't go to bed angry.
Let them do what they want.

55
00:04:42,682 --> 00:04:44,115
"Dress sexy. "

56
00:04:44,784 --> 00:04:48,481
And all I kept thinking about was Daddy.
It's disgusting.

57
00:04:49,355 --> 00:04:53,257
Doesn't she know that?
That she ruined my life?

58
00:04:55,261 --> 00:04:57,422
Your father had a part in it.

59
00:04:58,798 --> 00:05:00,891
You don't think I know that?

60
00:05:02,435 --> 00:05:06,701
- Brooks is different than your father.
- I don't want to get married.

61
00:05:08,508 --> 00:05:13,502
Everything's pointing to the fact
that I shouldn't, and everybody knows.

62
00:05:14,147 --> 00:05:19,141
Brooks knows. His mother knows.
Do you know what she said to me?

63
00:05:21,321 --> 00:05:25,849
She said in India, if the wedding
doesn't take place at the appointed hour,

64
00:05:26,492 --> 00:05:28,119
they burn the bride.

65
00:05:28,227 --> 00:05:32,095
Just because she went to India
doesn't mean she's not an idiot.

66
00:05:32,231 --> 00:05:34,791
And Jane. If she's coming,

67
00:05:37,470 --> 00:05:38,937
I'm not going.

68
00:05:39,505 --> 00:05:43,703
She's coming, because your father's coming
and he paid for everything.

69
00:05:43,810 --> 00:05:46,745
You're having the wedding.
The bride will not be burned.

70
00:05:46,846 --> 00:05:49,246
Turn those earrings
into a tea service or something.

71
00:05:49,349 --> 00:05:51,214
- Aren't you listening to me?
- I am,

72
00:05:51,317 --> 00:05:54,081
and you're babbling like a little fool.
Go to your room.

73
00:05:54,220 --> 00:05:55,346
- What?
- You heard me.

74
00:05:55,455 --> 00:05:58,856
You want to act like a child,
I'll treat you like one.

75
00:06:04,831 --> 00:06:06,765
Would somebody get that?

76
00:06:14,307 --> 00:06:15,774
- Hello?
- Daddy?

77
00:06:17,210 --> 00:06:18,643
Are you alone?

78
00:06:18,778 --> 00:06:21,144
<i>- Yes, what's wrong?
- Nothing's right.</i>

79
00:06:21,247 --> 00:06:25,308
My bridesmaids are supposed to give me
something blue and something new.

80
00:06:25,418 --> 00:06:28,216
- Or Mommy. She should know that.
- Who?

81
00:06:28,888 --> 00:06:32,722
I don't like her, Daddy, and I've told you
I don't want her to be there.

82
00:06:33,426 --> 00:06:37,294
- Honey, put your mother on the phone.
- He wants to talk to you.

83
00:06:44,303 --> 00:06:45,964
You have to keep Jane under control.

84
00:06:46,072 --> 00:06:48,233
Well, first of all, tell the bride
that everything is copacetic.

85
00:06:48,341 --> 00:06:50,969
We both agree that she's nuts
and she should shut up.

86
00:06:51,811 --> 00:06:55,042
Your father said that he's sorry
and that Jane will stay out of your way

87
00:06:55,148 --> 00:06:58,117
- and that we're both tired of the drama.
- He said all that?

88
00:06:58,217 --> 00:07:00,447
I'm not playing chicken anymore.
If she wants to cancel the wedding,

89
00:07:00,553 --> 00:07:02,350
I'll take the deposit out of her inheritance.

90
00:07:03,022 --> 00:07:05,388
- He said the wedding's off.
- Fine.

91
00:07:06,058 --> 00:07:09,027
You mean that?
You're not worried about India?

92
00:07:09,328 --> 00:07:12,923
- Why are you doing this?
- Do you want to cancel it or not?

93
00:07:14,867 --> 00:07:15,993
No.

94
00:07:16,102 --> 00:07:19,697
Then go eat something.
I'm not taking that dress in again.

95
00:07:25,645 --> 00:07:28,512
Why did Jane get her
such an expensive gift?

96
00:07:29,415 --> 00:07:30,882
I didn't even know they saw each other.

97
00:07:31,083 --> 00:07:33,551
- Of course you didn't.
- I forbid it.

98
00:07:34,187 --> 00:07:37,315
- Can't wait to get her out of here.
- Everything okay?

99
00:07:39,258 --> 00:07:40,452
<i>Goodbye.</i>

100
00:07:42,261 --> 00:07:43,489
Goodbye.

101
00:07:44,697 --> 00:07:47,291
Jane! Get in here, now.

102
00:07:49,368 --> 00:07:51,962
- I didn't know you were home.
- I overdid it at lunch,

103
00:07:52,071 --> 00:07:53,800
as did you, I heard.

104
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:57,471
I'm sorry, sweetheart.
I just wanted to make amends.

105
00:07:57,577 --> 00:07:58,771
I got her a beautiful present.

106
00:07:58,878 --> 00:08:03,008
Why the hell are you even talking to her?
You're screwing things up!

107
00:08:03,115 --> 00:08:06,846
I'm tired of the awkwardness,
and I'm trying to be nice.

108
00:08:07,587 --> 00:08:10,647
And I don't know
what kind of world you live in,

109
00:08:11,057 --> 00:08:13,651
- but I am the good person here.
- You're not good,

110
00:08:13,759 --> 00:08:17,286
because you didn't listen to me
and you really upset her.

111
00:08:21,334 --> 00:08:23,666
Everything you do is for her.

112
00:08:25,171 --> 00:08:26,638
I'm your wife.

113
00:08:27,406 --> 00:08:29,738
And guess what?
I live here and I get to do what I want to do,

114
00:08:29,842 --> 00:08:32,868
so stop trying to tell me
that you know better.

115
00:08:37,083 --> 00:08:40,246
- You'd better not have locked that door.
- Go away!

116
00:08:40,853 --> 00:08:43,117
Or what? You'll commit suicide?

117
00:08:52,798 --> 00:08:56,529
- Peter, what are you doing home?
- I got fired.

118
00:08:59,205 --> 00:09:00,672
What happened?

119
00:09:02,842 --> 00:09:08,474
Lane told me Kenny is senior something
of something accounts and I'm not.

120
00:09:09,749 --> 00:09:11,580
I'm account something.

121
00:09:13,619 --> 00:09:17,919
I couldn't even hear him.
All I saw was his frog-like mouth flapping.

122
00:09:18,858 --> 00:09:21,759
- So, did he ask you to leave?
- No.

123
00:09:24,397 --> 00:09:27,798
I have to ask this,
but did you lose your temper?

124
00:09:29,068 --> 00:09:30,501
No, I didn't.

125
00:09:31,370 --> 00:09:34,066
That's good. That's very good.

126
00:09:35,975 --> 00:09:40,378
Do you remember if he said anything
about how much they want you to stay?

127
00:09:40,913 --> 00:09:43,814
- No.
- That's good, too. So it didn't come up.

128
00:09:44,383 --> 00:09:46,943
Trudy, stop it with the Ellery Queen.

129
00:09:51,023 --> 00:09:53,719
- I'm going to call Duck.
- No, you're not.

130
00:09:54,327 --> 00:09:56,522
They would have fired you
if they wanted to fire you.

131
00:09:56,629 --> 00:09:59,189
You need to wait and see how it goes.

132
00:09:59,966 --> 00:10:04,198
He basically said I care too much
about my clients and they notice it.

133
00:10:04,737 --> 00:10:06,568
How could that be bad?

134
00:10:08,074 --> 00:10:11,305
Peter, you hold all the cards.

135
00:10:15,948 --> 00:10:17,779
It's going to be fine.

136
00:10:39,271 --> 00:10:41,034
I thought you'd left.

137
00:10:41,407 --> 00:10:43,875
- I'm here.
- I see.

138
00:10:48,280 --> 00:10:51,374
- Well, thank you.
- I've done it before.

139
00:10:54,153 --> 00:10:55,643
Go back to bed.

140
00:11:05,665 --> 00:11:08,793
- Do you want anything?
- No. I'll be in, in a bit.

141
00:11:16,575 --> 00:11:21,478
- It's got to be 100 degrees in here.
- You ask the building for heat, you get heat.

142
00:11:22,048 --> 00:11:23,913
<i>Mr. Herman on line one.</i>

143
00:11:26,919 --> 00:11:29,683
- Hello? Can you give me a minute?
- No.

144
00:11:30,256 --> 00:11:33,521
I'm right around the corner
at the Elysée, room 531.

145
00:11:35,127 --> 00:11:39,757
- I'm in the middle of something.
- Pee wee, sweetheart, it's been three weeks.

146
00:11:39,999 --> 00:11:43,867
You can get room service. I think they have
a Monte Cristo sandwich. You love that.

147
00:11:44,570 --> 00:11:46,538
I'm having lunch with Kurt and Smitty.

148
00:11:46,672 --> 00:11:48,970
They're a couple of homos.
Tell them you have plans.

149
00:11:53,212 --> 00:11:56,909
- It's kind of short notice.
- Come on, Creative, be creative.

150
00:12:03,789 --> 00:12:05,882
I have to go to the printer.

151
00:12:07,026 --> 00:12:10,621
- I know a nooner when I hear one.
- You're disgusting.

152
00:12:11,731 --> 00:12:13,892
<i>No, Bob did.</i>

153
00:12:14,900 --> 00:12:15,924
<i>Bob?</i>

154
00:12:16,435 --> 00:12:18,460
I was hoping to catch you
on your way to lunch.

155
00:12:18,571 --> 00:12:19,799
Too late.

156
00:12:21,040 --> 00:12:24,942
<i>- I must say I'm surprised.
- Frankly, I was a little suspicious...</i>

157
00:12:25,044 --> 00:12:29,743
I found out yesterday that head of accounts
is going to Kenny and his haircut.

158
00:12:30,015 --> 00:12:31,983
<i>- I heard.
- This is the first time he's invited her here...</i>

159
00:12:32,084 --> 00:12:34,609
- Can you turn that off?
- Not really.

160
00:12:36,322 --> 00:12:38,620
<i>Did you ask him why he invited her?</i>

161
00:12:38,724 --> 00:12:43,127
<i>He said something about not wanting her
to actually have to get involved.</i>

162
00:12:43,662 --> 00:12:46,153
- Were you consulted?
- After the fact.

163
00:12:48,367 --> 00:12:52,064
- What does it mean?
- It's not good.

164
00:12:53,773 --> 00:12:57,607
I know it's not good.
There's no future for me here.

165
00:12:59,779 --> 00:13:03,044
- How did you do it? You made your job up.
- I didn't.

166
00:13:03,282 --> 00:13:05,546
I looked at other agencies
and saw that they had TV departments

167
00:13:05,651 --> 00:13:06,811
and wondered why we didn't.

168
00:13:06,919 --> 00:13:10,082
Well, there's no such thing
in the accounts field.

169
00:13:10,356 --> 00:13:13,154
- There's marketing.
- That's a research job.

170
00:13:16,162 --> 00:13:18,027
- Is this official?
- Yes.

171
00:13:18,564 --> 00:13:20,691
I'm afraid we can't hire Mr. Charcot.

172
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:23,963
Well, at least you had the guts
to send me a memo.

173
00:13:24,069 --> 00:13:27,334
- He's far too expensive.
- Salvatore Romano is gone.

174
00:13:27,506 --> 00:13:29,565
There is no one in charge
of the art department.

175
00:13:29,675 --> 00:13:32,200
I haven't heard a complaint
from any of the clients.

176
00:13:32,311 --> 00:13:36,680
- Jesus! It's hotter in here than in my office.
- That's because you're overexcited.

177
00:13:36,782 --> 00:13:38,977
Do you want me to walk you through
a delivery schedule?

178
00:13:43,389 --> 00:13:46,051
<i>This is Walter Cronkite in our newsroom,</i>

179
00:13:47,293 --> 00:13:49,591
<i>and there has been an attempt,
as perhaps you know now,</i>

180
00:13:49,695 --> 00:13:51,219
<i>on the life of President Kennedy.</i>

181
00:13:51,330 --> 00:13:55,892
<i>He was wounded in an automobile driving
from Dallas Airport into downtown Dallas</i>

182
00:13:56,001 --> 00:13:58,026
<i>along with Governor Connally of Texas.</i>

183
00:13:58,137 --> 00:14:00,401
<i>They've been taken
to Parkland Hospital there,</i>

184
00:14:00,506 --> 00:14:02,906
<i>where their condition is as yet...</i>

185
00:14:09,381 --> 00:14:11,872
My God, how much
have you been smoking in here?

186
00:14:11,984 --> 00:14:13,576
Sorry about that.

187
00:14:18,958 --> 00:14:23,122
- I'm glad you ran over.
- Me too.

188
00:14:26,498 --> 00:14:29,558
I don't understand. I can't run
my department without an art director.

189
00:14:29,668 --> 00:14:34,002
- You want to call Saint John?
- Bert Cooper still has a say around here.

190
00:14:43,082 --> 00:14:44,982
Hello. What?

191
00:14:45,484 --> 00:14:48,351
If they wanted to fire you,
they would've fired you.

192
00:14:48,454 --> 00:14:50,183
I'm gonna die at this desk, unnoticed.

193
00:14:50,289 --> 00:14:53,622
Do you have any idea
what I've done for this company?

194
00:14:54,026 --> 00:14:55,015
- What are you doing?
- Christ!

195
00:14:55,127 --> 00:14:56,185
- Somebody shot the president.
- Turn on the TV.

196
00:14:56,295 --> 00:14:57,387
What?

197
00:14:58,898 --> 00:15:01,298
<i>...top of the president's car was down.</i>

198
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:03,561
<i>They drew their pistols,
but the damage was done.</i>

199
00:15:03,669 --> 00:15:05,261
<i>- Oh, my God. Unbelievable.
- The president was slumped over</i>

200
00:15:05,371 --> 00:15:07,498
<i>in the backseat of the car, face down,</i>

201
00:15:07,606 --> 00:15:10,541
<i>then Governor Connally,
after slumping to the left for a moment,</i>

202
00:15:10,643 --> 00:15:12,873
<i>lay on the floor of the rear seats.</i>

203
00:15:12,978 --> 00:15:14,445
- Oh, my God.
- Dear God.

204
00:15:14,546 --> 00:15:15,877
Is he dead?

205
00:15:28,627 --> 00:15:30,618
What the hell is going on?

206
00:15:37,069 --> 00:15:41,972
<i>Every person listening at this moment
has flashed back to that day in April, 1945,</i>

207
00:15:42,675 --> 00:15:45,405
<i>when Franklin Delano Roosevelt...</i>

208
00:15:45,511 --> 00:15:49,447
<i>Excuse me, Chet, here is a flash
from the Associated Press, dateline Dallas.</i>

209
00:15:49,548 --> 00:15:51,812
<i>Two priests
who were with President Kennedy</i>

210
00:15:51,917 --> 00:15:54,215
<i>say he is dead of bullet wounds.</i>

211
00:15:54,420 --> 00:15:58,413
<i>There is no further confirmation,
but this is what we have on a flash basis...</i>

212
00:15:58,524 --> 00:16:01,550
- Is he okay?
- They just said he died.

213
00:16:01,660 --> 00:16:03,594
<i>Two priests in Dallas
who were with President Kennedy</i>

214
00:16:03,696 --> 00:16:05,994
<i>say he is dead of bullet wounds.</i>

215
00:16:06,165 --> 00:16:08,133
<i>- Oh, lord.
- There is no further confirmation.</i>

216
00:16:08,233 --> 00:16:13,261
<i>This is the only word we have indicating
the president may, in fact, have lost his life.</i>

217
00:16:13,372 --> 00:16:16,830
<i>It has just moved
on the Associated Press wires from Dallas.</i>

218
00:16:16,942 --> 00:16:20,378
<i>The two priests were called to the hospital
to administer the last rites...</i>

219
00:16:20,479 --> 00:16:21,969
<i>- Oh, my goodness.
... of the Roman Catholic Church,</i>

220
00:16:22,081 --> 00:16:24,481
<i>- and it is from them we get the word...
- I know.</i>

221
00:16:24,583 --> 00:16:26,073
<i>...that the president has died,</i>

222
00:16:26,185 --> 00:16:29,154
<i>that the bullet wounds inflicted on him
as he rode in a motorcade</i>

223
00:16:29,254 --> 00:16:31,779
<i>through downtown Dallas have been fatal.</i>

224
00:16:31,890 --> 00:16:36,953
<i>We would remind you there is no official
confirmation of this from any source as yet.</i>

225
00:16:37,229 --> 00:16:39,060
<i>Bill, just moments before
you brought the flash,</i>

226
00:16:39,164 --> 00:16:40,256
