00:32:55,406 --> 00:32:59,035
She pulled through.
They pulled through. I pulled through.

442
00:33:03,815 --> 00:33:05,749
I can't believe how quiet it is out there.

443
00:33:05,850 --> 00:33:10,310
Not everywhere. Greg just called.
He's working the night shift at the ER.

444
00:33:12,123 --> 00:33:13,784
<i>People are still getting sick.</i>

445
00:33:13,891 --> 00:33:17,793
Car accidents are happening.
Babies are being born.

446
00:33:18,796 --> 00:33:22,527
Well, I'm glad he's not home.
I had to talk to you.

447
00:33:28,139 --> 00:33:30,403
Nobody else is saying
the right thing about this.

448
00:33:30,742 --> 00:33:32,733
My God, you're really upset.

449
00:33:33,911 --> 00:33:35,538
What's that about?

450
00:33:37,115 --> 00:33:39,743
Because there's nothing funny about this.

451
00:33:46,691 --> 00:33:49,660
Well, hang in there, red.

452
00:33:50,428 --> 00:33:51,622
You too.

453
00:33:54,198 --> 00:33:56,325
<i>- Bye-bye.
- Goodbye.</i>

454
00:34:05,043 --> 00:34:08,479
<i>Put him on a standby
of indeterminate length, will you?</i>

455
00:34:10,114 --> 00:34:12,105
<i>Let me have it. I want it.</i>

456
00:34:13,151 --> 00:34:15,949
<i>Being led out by Captain Fritz.</i>

457
00:34:16,921 --> 00:34:20,948
<i>There is the prisoner. There is Lee Oswald.</i>

458
00:34:23,428 --> 00:34:24,452
<i>He's been shot.</i>

459
00:34:24,562 --> 00:34:26,427
- Oh, my God. Oh, my God.
- What happened?

460
00:34:26,531 --> 00:34:27,657
<i>Lee Oswald has been shot.</i>

461
00:34:27,765 --> 00:34:30,928
They shot him. The police were walking him
through the building

462
00:34:31,035 --> 00:34:33,765
- and some man ran up and shot him.
- What?

463
00:34:34,772 --> 00:34:36,137
<i>Detectives have their guns drawn.</i>

464
00:34:36,240 --> 00:34:38,936
<i>- What is going on?
- Oswald has been shot.</i>

465
00:34:40,111 --> 00:34:42,443
<i>There is no question about it.
Oswald has been shot.</i>

466
00:34:42,547 --> 00:34:45,277
- Please, leave me alone.
- Betts?

467
00:34:45,383 --> 00:34:48,352
<i>...here in the basement
of Dallas police headquarters.</i>

468
00:34:48,453 --> 00:34:49,920
What happened?

469
00:34:50,855 --> 00:34:54,291
<i>- Do you know where he is at present?
- No, sir, I don't.</i>

470
00:34:56,060 --> 00:34:59,655
<i>- Can you give us some indication...
- Nothing. Go upstairs.</i>

471
00:35:05,837 --> 00:35:08,203
<i>The family, incidentally,
asked that there be no flowers,</i>

472
00:35:08,306 --> 00:35:10,171
<i>but there have, nevertheless, been flowers.</i>

473
00:35:10,274 --> 00:35:13,334
<i>People either didn't hear
or chose to ignore it,</i>

474
00:35:13,511 --> 00:35:17,845
<i>and one room or two rooms
in the White House have had to be set aside</i>

475
00:35:20,051 --> 00:35:24,613
<i>to hold them. The casket, incidentally,</i>

476
00:35:24,822 --> 00:35:27,814
<i>will remain closed at all times
during all ceremonies...</i>

477
00:35:27,925 --> 00:35:29,392
I'm going out.

478
00:35:33,865 --> 00:35:35,662
- Where?
- For a drive.

479
00:35:37,401 --> 00:35:41,963
Let me drive. I'll get the kids.
We'll all go somewhere. That's a good idea.

480
00:35:42,106 --> 00:35:45,269
No. I need to clear my head.

481
00:35:45,643 --> 00:35:48,339
<i>...airports, four of them around town...</i>

482
00:36:16,307 --> 00:36:20,539
- I'm so glad you could see me.
- Where does your husband think you are?

483
00:36:21,445 --> 00:36:26,280
I don't care. He's been lying to me for years.
I couldn't be in that house.

484
00:36:29,520 --> 00:36:33,854
Then I saw you yesterday.
I didn't know you were going to be there.

485
00:36:35,893 --> 00:36:37,952
I hoped you would be there.

486
00:36:38,629 --> 00:36:43,430
Derby day, it seems like 100 years ago.

487
00:36:47,205 --> 00:36:50,641
And then this morning,
seeing that man shot to death...

488
00:36:53,110 --> 00:36:54,702
What is going on?

489
00:36:55,046 --> 00:36:59,449
It will be okay. We've lost a lot of presidents
and we're still standing.

490
00:37:00,351 --> 00:37:04,811
I wish I could believe you.
I can't believe anything right now.

491
00:37:06,457 --> 00:37:09,688
Have you thought that
there are other ways to live?

492
00:37:12,296 --> 00:37:15,732
Listen. I'm not in love
with the tragedy of this thing.

493
00:37:16,667 --> 00:37:19,795
<i>It's not Romeo and Juliet.
I want it to happen.</i>

494
00:37:21,272 --> 00:37:23,103
I have three children.

495
00:37:23,441 --> 00:37:27,172
I'll know more when the primaries
start to shake out in spring,

496
00:37:27,278 --> 00:37:31,510
- but I can leave the campaign right now.
- I don't want you to do that.

497
00:37:39,991 --> 00:37:42,289
You don't have to answer me now,

498
00:37:43,427 --> 00:37:45,361
but I want to marry you.

499
00:37:50,167 --> 00:37:53,432
- I don't know what to say.
- You don't have to say anything.

500
00:37:53,537 --> 00:37:54,868
I told you.

501
00:37:55,773 --> 00:38:00,870
But if you search your heart,
you'll know that I can make you happy.

502
00:38:21,265 --> 00:38:22,630
I should go.

503
00:38:24,935 --> 00:38:27,995
I wish I could take you
to the movies right now,

504
00:38:28,939 --> 00:38:31,999
that some theater was playing
your favorite movie.

505
00:38:34,945 --> 00:38:36,674
<i>Singin' in the Rain.</i>

506
00:38:37,815 --> 00:38:40,841
Well, just think about that.

507
00:39:02,973 --> 00:39:08,104
<i>This is made possible by special equipment,
and it will move at one-fourth speed.</i>

508
00:39:08,479 --> 00:39:11,107
<i>So we would like to show you
the slow motion of the shooting</i>

509
00:39:11,215 --> 00:39:13,183
<i>of Lee Harvey Oswald now.</i>

510
00:39:15,920 --> 00:39:17,751
They just stood there.

511
00:39:17,922 --> 00:39:20,789
No security.
The most wanted man in America.

512
00:39:21,692 --> 00:39:25,093
Why even have a trial?
Just throw him over to the mob.

513
00:39:25,563 --> 00:39:29,863
<i>Now you can see the two detectives,
one in a light suit, one in a dark,</i>

514
00:39:30,468 --> 00:39:31,560
<i>bringing Oswald out.</i>

515
00:39:31,669 --> 00:39:35,002
<i>The camera changes its lens
for a close-up of Oswald.</i>

516
00:39:36,841 --> 00:39:40,106
<i>The shot has been fired. You cannot hear it
in this version of the tape.</i>

517
00:39:40,211 --> 00:39:42,076
<i>Oswald falls.
The man with the hat moves in on him.</i>

518
00:39:42,179 --> 00:39:44,545
<i>He's grabbed by the man in light.</i>

519
00:39:46,250 --> 00:39:49,777
- You're not going into work tomorrow?
- No, of course not.

520
00:39:50,321 --> 00:39:54,280
- It's a national day of mourning.
- You're going to go in Tuesday.

521
00:39:55,826 --> 00:39:58,021
There's another happy thought.

522
00:39:59,864 --> 00:40:04,164
Those people don't care about you.
And honestly, what's the difference?

523
00:40:04,468 --> 00:40:06,197
What are you saying?

524
00:40:07,171 --> 00:40:11,039
You did everything they asked you to do,
but you don't owe them anything.

525
00:40:11,142 --> 00:40:14,509
<i>...minutes past 2:00 Eastern Standard Time,
we were advised</i>

526
00:40:14,612 --> 00:40:19,174
<i>that Lee Harvey Oswald was dead.
Now Ruby is under arrest...</i>

527
00:40:19,784 --> 00:40:24,346
You should start gathering your clients.
They'll follow you wherever you go.

528
00:40:24,989 --> 00:40:27,389
<i>...is the operator of two nightclubs
in Dallas...</i>

529
00:40:28,993 --> 00:40:32,520
<i>The only other president buried there
is William Howard Taft,</i>

530
00:40:32,630 --> 00:40:36,999
<i>though, of course, there are many
other heroes of perhaps lesser renown.</i>

531
00:40:37,334 --> 00:40:40,792
<i>That is the Lee... Robert E. Lee Mansion.</i>

532
00:40:41,105 --> 00:40:45,906
<i>Its name, Arlington, has been given
to the cemetery and, in fact, to the county.</i>

533
00:40:46,076 --> 00:40:48,636
<i>- Francine has the kids.
- The president's brother, Robert Kennedy,</i>

534
00:40:48,746 --> 00:40:51,442
<i>and the Secretary of Defense,
Robert McNamara...</i>

535
00:40:51,549 --> 00:40:54,643
- I don't know where to begin.
- What?

536
00:40:58,956 --> 00:41:04,121
I want to scream at you
for ruining all of this.

537
00:41:07,998 --> 00:41:12,765
But then you try to fix it
and there's no point.

538
00:41:15,172 --> 00:41:17,003
There's no point, Don.

539
00:41:21,979 --> 00:41:24,277
You're very upset. I understand.

540
00:41:27,051 --> 00:41:30,612
I know it's painful, but it's going to pass.

541
00:41:33,624 --> 00:41:36,650
- I don't love you.
- Betts, don't.

542
00:41:38,896 --> 00:41:41,194
- You're distraught.
- That's true,

543
00:41:42,666 --> 00:41:44,827
but I don't love you anymore.

544
00:41:47,538 --> 00:41:49,403
- I know that.
- Stop it.

545
00:41:50,307 --> 00:41:53,743
<i>- I kissed you yesterday.
- Kennedy's remains...</i>

546
00:41:53,844 --> 00:41:55,675
I didn't feel a thing.

547
00:41:56,347 --> 00:41:59,976
<i>...the public allowed to pass through
and pay its respects.</i>

548
00:42:00,084 --> 00:42:02,348
<i>There will be a little roped...</i>

549
00:42:02,453 --> 00:42:05,149
You'll feel better tomorrow. You'll see.

550
00:42:06,524 --> 00:42:08,890
You can't even hear me right now.

551
00:42:09,527 --> 00:42:10,960
You're right.

552
00:42:13,063 --> 00:42:15,361
<i>...on Monday it will be taken</i>

553
00:42:15,466 --> 00:42:20,165
<i>to the St. Matthew's Cathedral, which is on
Rhode Island Avenue in Washington,</i>

554
00:42:20,871 --> 00:42:22,429
<i>for the funeral.</i>

555
00:42:24,942 --> 00:42:29,311
<i>This, I think, is the largest
Catholic cathedral in town.</i>

556
00:42:29,413 --> 00:42:31,881
<i>It is, as you see, draped in black.</i>

557
00:42:32,249 --> 00:42:35,946
<i>It's been open all day.
Great numbers of people have stopped...</i>

558
00:43:30,908 --> 00:43:32,876
- Morning.
- Morning, Daddy.

559
00:43:33,010 --> 00:43:34,443
Good morning.

560
00:43:39,249 --> 00:43:42,685
- Where are you going?
- I have to go to work. I'm sorry.

561
00:43:43,053 --> 00:43:45,681
- It's cold outside.
- I'm fine.

562
00:44:16,920 --> 00:44:18,046
Peggy.

563
00:44:23,827 --> 00:44:25,761
What are you doing here?

564
00:44:26,764 --> 00:44:28,629
I don't know. Aqua Net.

565
00:44:37,775 --> 00:44:40,539
It doesn't shoot till after Thanksgiving.

566
00:44:42,179 --> 00:44:43,646
We'll be okay.

567
00:44:52,423 --> 00:44:54,015
What do you have?

568
00:44:54,158 --> 00:44:57,184
- What are you doing here?
- The bars are closed.

569
00:44:59,863 --> 00:45:03,355
My roommate invited over half the building
so they could watch TV

570
00:45:03,467 --> 00:45:06,129
and write condolence letters to Jackie.

571
00:45:07,037 --> 00:45:10,200
Then I went to my sister's
and my mother was crying

572
00:45:10,307 --> 00:45:12,036
and praying so hard.

573
00:45:12,910 --> 00:45:16,141
There wasn't room
for anyone else to feel anything.

574
00:45:20,050 --> 00:45:22,245
The funeral's already started.

575
00:45:22,920 --> 00:45:26,321
I was going to watch in Cooper's office.
Is that okay?

576
00:45:27,624 --> 00:45:28,648
Yes.

577
00:45:35,766 --> 00:45:37,256
Are you coming?